Came here to pick up a pastry box collab between Melissa Weller and SmittenKitchen (it was amazing!). The staff was fantastic and super friendly. We decided to grab lattes to go and mine (oat milk) and his (local whole milk😍) were both fantastic. The espresso used had a delicious flavor and was roasted perfectly. It’s a good latte when all it needs is the steamed milk.  I look forward to trying more of their fare.

Known as a place “to eat early and drink late”, Gertie is a lovely place delivering good food every day! They are a great restaurant in a town full of great restaurants, but what separates them from the rest is their social engagement. They prepare 1,500 hundred meals per week for distribution to underserved communities across New York City! Run by Nate Adler (Huertas), Will Edwards (Marlow Collective) and Flip Biddelman (Flip Biddelman (Huertas)), the result is a gorgeous 70-seat lorimer L train Seat to celebrate the birth and growth of Adler's grandmother in Queens. Here, a small but stylish lunch restaurant restaurant made for 2019. Check out the unchanging mural designed by artist Lea Carey. For brunch, you will find egg'n' cheese on bialys (made in-house by Savannah Turley), on Gertie Breakfast (two sunny eggs, white beans, vegetables and toast) and pumpkin toast. At lunch, the bread rolls include rotisserie meat, provolone cheese, lettuce and Italian seasonings, smoked fish dishes (melted cheddar cheese on white salmon salad and cheddar cheese), and cauliflower melt (spicy cauliflower, Pickled chili and cheese sauce) sesame sourdough). For dinner, you can look forward to more rotisserie and pancakes as well as homemade syrup highball drinks.
This is a great place! The food is incredible, and there is a nice, socially distanced patio.
One of three Popeyes on staten Island. always crowded go early or order early. They sell out and when they run out,they run out!
Excellent casual dining. Fresh, comforting food with a sophisticated twist. Impressive wine selection. Charming enclosed garden.

5 stars for the amazing food - Jewish deli meets new American deliciousness.  I wish they were able to be open more frequently during the pandemic but just go Thursday - Sunday for breakfast or lunch!! They have a new pastry chef. I can’t wait for them to reopen inside as the space is so lovely and bright. Back patio seating.
They have a great cold weather patio set up. Great food always, and right now have a visiting pastry chef (I think for the month?) making these incredible pastries. Get there early bc they sell out!

Gertie's is doing some kind of pastry magic right now - really delicious! A friend gifted us a pastry box, which was an amazing assortment of tasty goods (the shnecken!) and already we are thinking about the next one. Great gift, too.

The food here is disgusting and almost criminal. I wouldn’t recommend it to anyone. I ordered a chicken sandwich and the meat that was there was brown and the whole thing was inedibly burned. The “fries” were potatoes that had most of the insides scooped out. They were burned, yet soggy. Bizarre.
One of my favorite restaurants in Williamsburg. Phenomenal vibe, awesome food and drinks are on-point. The Big Salad is my favorite - changes seasonally and is absolutely delicious.

Split a Bialy with Salmon and a Chicken Schnitzel sandwich. Both were delicious, as was the coffee. A cool outdoor setting as well

Very good quality of food and I totally recommend the schnitzel. The seasoning and the fries are amazing. Also the cocktails are very good and the service is very nice. They have a really comfy patio.

The food was interesting. There are a few different great options if you are looking for something familiar with a new spin. The drink option were not as good. If you are looking for wine by the glass the selection options are limited. However, wine by the bottle is in abundance.
I ordered from caviar. First time my order was late 2 hours. Today 3. Food is good but the only thing consistent here is the poor customer service.

Just had a pickeup order for dinner and everything was 5 stars - chicken, rice, cukes, green beans, and cauliflower. Actually I want to marry the cauliflower. Wine and beer are fantastic too. Can't wait to visit the dining room for brunch again soon!

Great spot for breakfast. Order at the counter and they will bring it to your table. The staff was friendly and helpful and seemed to go out of their way to make us feel welcomed. The bialy was delicious and the grilled muffin was an unexpected treat. Can’t wait to try this place in the evening.

Enjoyed our brunch here. Love the casual atmosphere and delicious food. We sat at the bar & got to watch the chefs at work. I got the breakfast sandwich with bacon and the hubby got the Bialy. While it doesn’t seem like a lot of food it’s immensely satisfying.
Great food. Chicken is delicious. Drinks are fun and inventive. Love the atmosphere and friendly staff

So I want desperately to give this place a higher rating because of the super friendly staff and lovely space... But it’s overpriced for what it is and I would not recommend the Bialy 🙈 I’m sorry, Gertie 😭
Great neighborhood spot. I’m a regular for lunch and breakfast!
Fabulous food ! Best food tasted in nyc, especially muffins and coffee

Four stars for the food and one star for the unexpected joy of complex food made to seem simple. The winter salad was simple what it was dressed with was not. What it was.......was light and peppery. The half duck on a bed of fried rice? Transporting that's all I can say. The ending? Great vanilla ice cream topping a homemade chocolate chip cookie. A wondrous finish. Worth the trip.....and another trip back.

Gertie is a warm, lively, inventive jewel of an eatery. The wine list is creative and unique. The menu is short but varied enough for most every taste. The Blue Plate Special Pot Pie is reason enough to cross a bridge or a continent to taste. Bravo!
I loved this place. Food was great and ambiance was excellent. def coming back :)

Huge disappointment considering the high reviews. Took 15 minutes to be seated and after ordering at the counter we still waited another 45 for our food to be served. Food was cold and overall mediocre at best. The cold brew was solid, but not soectacular and the same goes for the lattes. The fact that me and 2 friends paid 60$ to wait around an hour for food that was cold is a little ridiculous. Staff was nice and friendly and the location is cool but definitely not with coming back due to the slow service and subpar food.

I was so looking forward to this given the great reviews online. Unfortunately the heating didn't work the whole evening and all the guests had to keep their down jackets on. I get that this may have been out of their control but no one from the staff let us know or made any suggestions on making it more comfortable or making up for it, i.e. no hot drinks, blankets etc were offered - even after asking. On top, we were a larger group of +6  and had to do a pre fix menu because of that. I don't mind a pre fix but what they ended up doing was just bringing out 2-3 plates of food in the middle of the table - far less food than what would have been on individual plates. For example we ended up getting 3 cookies and 3 pieces of pie for 9 folks - but had to pay the pre fix price per person - not cool in our opinion.
Had a very subpar lunch here last week. The space is beautiful though.
Amazing place with great food. The ambiance is perfect.
Portions are really small. $15 for half a sandwich.

The place looks great, the food is very good and the people who work there are consistently very nice and welcoming. While I do echo some of the concerns about edging on overly seasoned food from some other reviewers, I happen to love it that way. Certainly if you have an aversion to strong tastes, this may not be totally for you. I happen to to go to Gertie almost exclusively for lunch during the week and find the experience extremely satisfying and, while not cheap by any stretch, totally worth it.
The chicken is excellent.

Coziest breakfast/brunch place in Williamsburg! Definitely recommended.  We have been here multiple times because the menu contained too many tasty options to try in one sitting. It is a nice homy restaurant with massive windows drawing in plenty of daylight.  We tried the Gertie breakfast, granola yoghurt, a rhubarb toast, some sides and almost all of the baked goodies (we recommend taking the jackpot; i.e four baked goodies). Oh and did you know you get a free refill of your coffee?!
Fantastic, absolutely fantastic. Great music, nice people and the food is the best I had all week in NYC. Had a pulled pork sandwich with dressed lettuce on the side. Would definitely recommend.
Wow, this place! Not only were the drinks amazing (lots of cocktails on draft), but the food was fantastic. Get the relish plate, you won't regret it.

Love this place. Great food/drink, well though-out space, and such a good team of people running it. Highly recommend.

Looove it! Baked goods and bread are amazing. Hard to find something like this around. Every detail is thought out and everything looks pretty. I love the big salad and the whitefish melt (pictures), but everything I tried has been tasty. Go before it’s impossible to get a seat.

I don’t like having to write a negative review but there is nothing positive I can say about this place. Visited a few times unfortunately and each one disappoints. Coffee is void of taste. Their menu is the most confused thing I’ve ever seen. Eggs and white beans do not belong together. Vastly over priced. Service based on the Basil Fawlty school (last visit our drinks arrived after we finished eating). Sorry to say but don’t waste your time or money.

LOVE the decor. Was busy but not crowded on a Saturday at 1pm. Food was delicious and fairly priced. They also have a nice outdoor space. The green juice was very bitter and the system of seating was a little confusing but I’d still go back!
Nice atmosphere

I went here for a private event where a custom menu was created to be inspired by a book. The chef at Gertie is a phenomenal talent. Everything was absolutely delicious and perfectly seasoned, cooked, and served. Everything was family-style and it made for a fantastic experience getting to know new people. This a hidden gem and I will absolutely be back.
Amazing service and food!
Breakfast sandwiches were great, place is cool. They have a nice breakfast beer for sunday brunches.

We went for the recently opened dinner service and were lucky enough to snag a Poppy's Duck (even though we hadn't ordered ahead). We'll get back to that in a second.  Gertie is everything a modern neighborhood regulars spot should be. They have a cute outdoor space, an amazing Cocktail program with smashable staples you could drink every day of the week, an amazingly friendly staff, and the order from an app (or at the counter) combined with the rotisserie means that you can eat as quickly (or slowly) as you like.  The wine list is small but great, and if you ask them, they'll take you down to their cellar and let you look around a small number of off menu options (currently including an amazing organic Grenache from Oregon which goes particularly well with the duck).  Now back to the duck. The flavor is amazing on both the breast and the confit leg, the house made sauces and scallion pancakes are amazing finishing touches. Easily one of the best duck preparations we've had in recent memory. Well worth calling ahead for. The cookies and cream dessert was also off the charts.
Delicious and filling. The staff is super nice too!!
So good!!!
Beautiful place, tasty and enjoyable!

Nice LA vibe to this place. You order at the counter and then sit down and wait for the food to be delivered at your table. I enjoyed everything we ate. The hash brown latkes are delicious. Egg sandwich was a little small maybe. The ingredients felt fresh and healthy. I’m looking forward to going back.

Cute millennial joint, unfortunately marred by inconsistent food. The matzo ball soup was so salty, I had to dilute it with hot water. The lentil walnut salad was the best dish in the greens and grains plate. The marinated fennel was dry. The sweet and sour celery was verging on the edge of overly seasoned.

Really adorable cafe with comfortable chairs and bright windows. Music is lively and chill. Mushroom melt is delicious and coffee is on point too. Everything is a little bit on the saltier side but still a really pleasant meal.

Such a pretty place to munch and chat—with a date or for a power lunch meeting. I came on a Monday around noon and it was buzzing, so I can only imagine what it’s like on the weekend. Their cauliflower patty melt was perfect, as were their homemade Oreos. Can’t wait to try the boozy sodas 😏
Was not impressed by the rude owner or very long wait after ordering. You have to queue to be seating, to order and then there was a long wait for the food. Disappointed.

I came here for brunch a few days after it opened. It has a lot of potential but they seemed to still be working out some kinks and the hostess just seemed confused the whole time.  The whole ordering, seating etc system was  very unclear, and we had to stand around for about 5 minutes before someone explained it to us. Given the unconventional system I think they should add some signage about it.  The hostess told us we could wait ~40 minutes for a table or sit at the bar. She assured us there were lots of seats at the bar so we went with that. However when we walked over there were no seats at the bar.... There were a couple at an awkwardly low table (coffee table height) next to the bar though, so we sat there and put in an order at the bar.  10 minutes later hostess comes over and asks if we are comfortable and says a table has opened up and offered we could sit there. However once she realized we had already ordered at the bar she said never mind, we needed to stay by the bar.  Overall I found the whole experience frustrating. We agreed to bar seats thinking we would actually be able to sit at the bar, and then resigned ourselves to the low table because we thought the wait for a real table would be way longer...  Anyway, onto the food. I got a breakfast sandwich and it was quite good. The food took 30+ minutes to come out though which I found surprising considering the menu is so small.  I would go back and try it again now that they have been at it for a weeks. Probably runs more smoothly now.
Good food
New favorite brunch place in Williamsburg! Location is perfect, SUN ALL day long and it's beautiful inside. Pastries are very tasty, huge and inexpensive ! Love it.
It was a bit slow but over all the food was good. Staff is friendly and kind. Will go again.

Loved this place.  Really solid simple food - excellent ingredients prepared well.  Loved the perfectly prepared fish, the baked greens, and the first rate apple pie, among other things.  Also has a great vibe - very welcoming and down to earth.  Agree with some of the journalists who likened it to Gjusta in LA.

Don’t sleep on Gertie’s dinner! We loved the cocktails (and the super interesting digestif selection), had the best cooked lamb I’ve had in a while, and loveddd the sweet and sour celery and smoked fish and chips. Can’t wait to grab a couple more friends to get back and try the duck! Service was amazing and the space is one I want to keep coming back to. New favorite, for sure.
Love this place. Great vibes and even better food. Can’t get enough!
Breakfast Sammy was sooooo good.  That english muffin rocks!   And the pickled peppers we perfection

The Veggie Gyro at Gertie might be my new favorite sandwich in New York right now. Filled with root vegetables, hot and white sauce, wrapped in a tasty,  thin, freshly grilled pita, you won’t miss that there’s no meat. It comes with a side of house made potato chips and pickles. If you’re hungry I’d also recommend grabbing a green or grain dish on the side.  We also tried the Chicken Salad Sandwich on Challah. Stuffed with tasty, chicken salad and topped with potato chips, it also comes with chips and pickle. The space is large with plenty of counter seating. A wall of windows makes it one of the brightest restaurants I’ve been to in a while. Recommend sitting at the counter so you can watch all the different dishes be prepared and plan what you’re going to get next time.

Dinner!  Smoked fish pate w/ crackers and hot sauce, lamb cooked perfectly with horseradish and garlic sauce, surprise favorite: braised celery.  Beautiful space, friendly staff, thoughtful & delicious food.
Great new addition to the neighborhood
The place you want to always come back to - great food, great staff, great everything.
Fresh bialeys and great coffee!

Everything about Gertie was perfect! Every item on the breakfast and lunch menu that we tried was excellent—delicious, creative, and there's ton of gluten-free, vegan, and vegetarian options (amongst all of the other breakfast classics!). The overall at vibe is airy, yet warm and homey and the whole team is top-notch. This is my new favorite spot in Williamsburg!
Everything we ordered was prepared promptly, looked beautiful, and tasted even greater. The space is beautifully designed and exudes a pleasant and calming atmosphere. Great place!
Amazing food, fun atmosphere... just awesome.
A great vibe and energy to this place, with even better food/coffee!
Got the breakfast sandwich with white sauce and it was fantastic.
Fun new restaurant with delicious food and great ambiance. Definitely will not disappoint.
This place is great! The food is awesome, the baked goods are awesome, the space is awesome and the people are awesome! Happy to have it in the neighborhood.

FANTASTIC. Best breakfast in the area. Baked goods on point, coffee on point, atmosphere on point. Squash toast makes avocado toast a thing of the past! Amazing breakfast sandwiches and bialys. So good that we just changed our plans to come back for lunch 😊
The pattie melt alone is worth the trip, but the bright open space with massive windows will make you want to stay all day. Plus all the other perfect items of the menu.
Gertie is incredible! Delicious food, awesome vibes, and super service.
